properties.headline: Winter Weather Advisory issued February 12 at 11:59AM CST until February 13 at 12:00PM CST by NWS Duluth MN
properties.description:
...DANGEROUS WIND CHILLS THIS MORNING THROUGH THURSDAY WITH
ACCUMULATING SNOW AND BLOWING SNOW ALONG THE SOUTH SHORE...

.Snow and lake effect snow will impact the South Shore today
through Thursday morning. The greatest snowfall accumulations of 3
to 7 inches are forecast for the northern portions of Ashland and
Iron counties, with lesser amounts of 2 to 5 inches elsewhere.
Blowing snow and dangerous wind chills to 35 below are also
expected.

Bitterly cold wind chills are expected across northeastern
Minnesota and northwestern Wisconsin this afternoon, and tonight
through Thursday morning. Wind chill values as low as -30 will be
possible across northeastern Minnesota this afternoon and evening.
Tonight into Thursday morning, widespread wind chill values
ranging from -20 to -40 are likely away from Lake Superior with
some values approaching -50 near the International Border.

* WHAT...Snow and lake effect snow. Additional snow accumulations
of 1 to 3 inches, except 4 to 6 inches for northern Iron and
Ashland counties.

* WHERE...Iron, Douglas, Bayfield and Ashland Counties. This
includes the Tribal Lands of the Red Cliff Band and the Bad
River Reservation.

* WHEN...Until noon CST Thursday.

* IMPACTS...Plan on slippery road conditions. Patchy blowing
snow could significantly reduce visibility. The hazardous
conditions could impact the morning or evening commute. The
dangerously cold wind chills as low as 35 below zero could
cause frostbite on exposed skin in as little as 10 minutes.
properties.instruction:
Slow down and use caution while traveling.

The latest road conditions can be obtained by calling 5 1 1.
Road conditions can also be found at 511mn.org for Minnesota or
511wi.gov for Wisconsin.

NWSheadline: WINTER WEATHER ADVISORY REMAINS IN EFFECT UNTIL NOON CST THURSDAY
